<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Lady Gaga and Ariana Grande put on a fierce performance at the 2020 MTV VMAs on Sunday evening - easily stealing the show.</p>

<p>Marking a bizarre return to awards season amid the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, the event was filmed over days at several different locations with production abiding by social distancing guidelines as it aired 'live' </p>

<p>The event was initially tipped to be hosted from Brooklyn's Barclays Center however a change in plans saw the show shifted to pre-records, despite MTV claiming much of the show would remain live. </p>

<p>The showstopping set was a medley of Gaga's songs including 911, Rain On Me, and Stupid Love, from her hit album Chromatica.</p>

<p>Making a statement on abiding by safety guidelines, Gaga, 34, wore a LED face mask throughout her set, as well as Ariana, 27, who wore a black silk mask, as she joined her for their hit For Rain On Me.</p>

